The Confederated Church of Canada was formed from the unification of the Anglican Church and the Ursuline See. The head of the Church is the Prime Minister, who also serves as an advisor to the Emperor of Canada.
On account of holy revelation, the Viceroy has declared there to be great oppression and persecution afar, and seeing such, has marched with intent to liberate.

column2: In the better days of the Californian Empire, the Evaluator of Merit was responsible for assessing all applicants for government positions. Today, as positions are usually filled by friends and relatives of rulers instead of qualified civil servants, the position of Evaluator of Merit is wholly ceremonial, but it still holds a good deal of prestige.
The Grand Herald is charged with greeting visitors to the court and ensuring they show proper respect to the ruler.
The Commandant of Gardens is responsible for the upkeep of the parks and waterways of the capital.
The Keeper of Equipages is responsible for maintaining the ruler's stable and keeping the roads clear for official business.
The Libationer is an essential part of court protocol, responsible for maintaining the royal vineyards, keeping the palace's wine cellar well stocked, and serving distinguished guests at the court.

The Amir al-Umara was once a title which signified supreme commander of all the commanders in the realm. Today, as positions are usually filled by the desired heir of rulers instead of qualified generals, the position is wholly ceremonial, but it still holds a good deal of authority.
This bishop is probably next in line for an Apostleship when one becomes available.
Of all the bishops in my realm, this one is the likeliest to get called as an Apostle.

The closest American equivalent to the government of the Japanese and Russian colonies is the merchant republic. However, unlike American merchant republics, the Japanese and Russian colonies do not have a tradition of religious freedom. The viceroyalty changes between the five major colonial families through special elections. Colonists can also build a network of Trade Posts, even in the counties of other powers.

The bureaucracy of California is similar to the Feudal system  rulers must rely on land holding vassals or varying loyalty and ambition. Rulers are allowed to reorganize their realm, revoking Prefectural titles and retracting vassals, but otherwise are not allowed to imprison vassals or revoke their titles unless they have broken the law. The maximum number of vassals and the number of Holdings you can directly own are controlled by the Centralization Law. If you should convert to a non-Cetic religion, your government form will change to Feudal.
column3: Le système arabe de l'Iqtâ est similaire au système féodal  les souverains doivent faire appel à des vassaux pour tenir leurs fiefs et leur degré d'ambition ou de loyauté peut varier. Le nombre maximal de vassaux et le nombre de fiefs que vous pouvez directement posséder sont contrôlés par la loi de centralisation. Cependant, il n'y a qu'une seule forme de succession disponible  la succession « ouverte » chaotique, selon laquelle le fils qui détient le plus de terres est en droit d'hériter. Si vous vous convertissez à une religion de type non musulman, votre gouvernement sera de type féodal.
column4: Das arabische Iqtasystem ähnelt dem Feudalsystem. Auch hier muss der Herrscher auf möglicherweise unzuverlässige Vasallen vertrauen. In den Zentralisierungsgesetzen ist festgelegt, wie viele Liegenschaften und wie viele Vasallen Ihr maximal haben könnt. Allerdings gibt es bei der Erbfolge nur eine einzige Variante: das chaotische 'offene' System, bei dem immer der Sohn mit dem größten Landbesitz erbt. Wenn Ihr zu einer nicht-islamischen Religion konvertiert, wechselt Eure Staatsform zum Feudalsystem.
column6: El sistema árabe del Iqta es similar al sistema feudal  los gobernantes deben depender de vasallos con posesiones territoriales de variable lealtad y ambición. El número máximo número de vasallos y de posesiones que puedes poseer directamente puedes poseer están controlados por la ley de centralización. Sin embargo, sólo existe una forma de sucesión: la caótica 'abierta', donde hereda el hijo con más tierras. Si te conviertes a una religión no musulmana tu forma de gobierno cambiará a feudal.

column2: Californian Imperialism, much like the ordinary Feudal government, revolves around vassals owing fealty to their liege who in this case is considered to be the divine Child of Heaven, and ruler of all. The Imperial government is unique to those who claim they are the true Emperor of California, and can only be implemented by an Emperor capable of backing this claim with force...
You will reform the Imperial bureaucracy of the Californian Empire.

Under Chinese Imperialism you:
§Y*§! Can hold cities
§Y*§! Do not care if others do not follow your religion nor can you demand their conversion
§Y*§! Do not get opinion penalties with vassals of other government types
§Y*§! Can not create or usurp Empires
§Y*§! Are limited to non-elective succession laws

the Knights of Columbus, and Knights of Peter Claver
the Keepers of the Green Peace
the Order of the Flaming Sword
This little bone is said to have come from a great saint.
A statue of the Virgin Mary. Every now and then, a drop of water or even blood will trickle down from the statue's eyes, in what can only be described as a miracle.
An ancient Old World document, written by The Founders. Much of the text is illegible, and the parchment is brittle to the touch.
An ancient bust of a Founder.
Glassware from the ancient world, finer than anything modern glassblowers can produce.
Jewelry from the ancient world, more intricate than anything modern artisans can produce.
An ancient, shiny device that contains the melodies of the Old World.
A fabulously preserved piece of Old World machinery, constructed of a miraculous metal and blessed so that it shall never rust.
This sacred bonsai is ancient beyond memory. Could it predate the Event?
Insightful pronouncements and decrees, penned in elaborate calligraphy by the Emperor himself.
A famous and well-preserved treatise, written by the first Emperor.
A piece of heavenly metal that fell to Earth.
The ashes of a Revelationist martyr, cremated in accordance with the ancient rites.
An enormous iron egg emblazoned with the sacred trefoil. When the time is right, it will hatch and Atomos will be reborn.
A holy mace once said to be wielded by the great warrior Plutos, servant to Fat Man. The metal used in crafting this weapon is said to be enchanted by Atomos.
A lovingly restored and functional pre-calamity firearm.
A functional pre-calamity mechanical calculating device.
A polished and ticking pre-calamity clockwork timekeeper.
A carefully maintained pre-calamity mechanical lettering device.
A restored and functional pre-calamity portable telescope.
A small collection of intact pre-calamity academic books.
A restored and functional pre-calamity magnetic compass.
The only piece of the raiment of Mictlantecuhtli left on Earth when he ascended from the underworld to assume his current place in the sky.
An enormous, steely-blue diamond. Some of its owners have met unfortunate ends, leading to rumors that it is cursed.
An egg-sized skull carved from a single enormous, flawless emerald. Some claim that it is imbued with divine power that wards its owner against harm.
A massive, smoothly polished star sapphire. It possesses a vivid blue color with a strikingly clear star, and is reputed to bring its owner vast wealth.
A trophy taken from a beast that was terrorizing the countryside. [This.GetBeastString]
A large silver chalice, engraved with the names of northern martyrs and holy warriors. You must be a victorious hero to drink its waters, lest your blood turn to ice in your veins.

Left behind by Archangel Michael after the Great Tribulation, this golden sword is said to have originated in God's armory. It would be blasphemy of the highest order to shed human blood with it, but as a ceremonial relic it proves divine right to rule.
The gleaming horn of the Archangel Gabriel, sounded to devastating effect at the onset of the Great Tribulation and left behind on Earth in preparation for the final doom that must eventually follow.

The mummified hand of Petrus Romanus, grasping the gavel of the dreadful judge. Although Petrus Romanus was destroyed when he placed his hand upon the gavel, humanity was spared and the final judgment postponed.
A staff of living wood, wrapped in vines of gold and topped with a pine cone. It has been kept alive for centuries, and blooms every year to announce the spring.

Given by Thunderbird to a great warrior in a time beyond living memory, the Thunderbird Whistle superficially resembles a ceremonial eagle bone whistle. A learned holy man can discern its true nature, and wield its power.
A set of sacred ritual objects, passed down through generations of holy people and handled only by them.
A golden idol of Oscar, an ancient guru famous for his long sermons concerning appreciativeness.

A reclining stone figure that functions as a sacrificial altar and as the throne of the rightful Emperor of All. It holds a bloody bowl and polished obsidian mirror, to allow a glimpse into the realm of the gods.
An ornate altar in the shape of a reclining man with his head turned to the side, holding a bowl that has received hundreds of human hearts.
A simple silver key.\nIt MUST NEVER be used.
Two seer stones, transparent and bound with silver into a pair of spectacles. Personally worn by Joseph Smith when he received divine revelations.
An instrument of revelation that allows the bearer to discern the will of God. It takes the form of a simple stone.
A fragment of the original temple in Nauvoo, preserved through the devastation of the Event.
A potent charm, inscribed with magic to ward off evil spirits.
A black granite tablet engraved with a timeless warning:\n"Do not call up that which you cannot put down."
Crown of the Lion of Judah
A golden leonine headdress, ancient beyond memory. It is an unmistakable symbol of power and sovereignty.
A golden leonine headdress, ancient beyond memory. It is an unmistakable symbol of power and sovereignty.
King Maxwell's famous iron shirt is an inspiration to all who seek to drive evil from the battlefield.

A sacred war banner that has been stained by blood many times, but has never once touched the ground. It holds the image of a black cat, an animal reviled by "civilized" faiths but revered as an omen of good luck by pagans.
A mummified monkey's paw reputed to fulfill the possessor's desires in costly, unnatural ways.
A disk of gold approximately twelve inches across, that predates the Event. It is inscribed with hundreds of fine grooves, as well as strange intricate hieroglyphs.
A large seven-branched menorah made of solid gold. It closely matches surviving descriptions of the menorah that once resided in the Holy Temple.

A white banner, adorned with a blue Star of David and flanked by two blue stripes. Although simple in design, it is nevertheless capable of inspiring Jewish warriors to fight bravely on the field of battle.

This handwritten Torah scroll, containing all 304,805 letters of the Hebrew Torah, was copied onto parchment long before the Event occurred. Pre-Event Sifrei Torah are highly sought after by Jewish religious and historical scholars alike.

This elaborate, jewel-encrusted crown was used by the antediluvian Catholic Church in their coronation ceremonies. It was rumored that a papal tiara was sent to Washington for safekeeping before the Deluge. These rumors have been confirmed.
A strangely well-crafted quern, bearing a striking resemblance to the Mill of Fortune. It is said to be able to produce gold, flour and salt from nothing at all.
column3: Un moulin à bras étrangement bien travaillé, ressemblant de façon frappante au Moulin de la Fortune. On dit qu'il est capable de produire de l'or, de la farine et du sel à partir de rien.
column4: Ein ungewöhnlich sorgfältig gearbeiteter Mühlstein mit einer verblüffenden Ähnlichkeit zur Zaubermühle. Wie es heißt, kann sie Gold, Mehl und Salz mahlen, ohne dass man sie jemals füllen müsste.
column6: Un molinillo de mano sumamente bien elaborado, con un parecido sorprendente al molinillo de la fortuna. Se dice que es capaz de fabricar oro, harina y sal de la nada.

column2: A piece of bark that has grown into the shape of a trio of visages. The trio's unsettling gazes pierce one's soul, almost as if some form of spirit still remains behind their eyes...
column3: Un morceau d'écorce qui a pris la forme de plusieurs visages. Les trois regards troublants transpercent l'âme, presque comme si une certaine forme d'esprit restait derrière leurs yeux...
column4: Ein Stück Rinde, das so gewachsen ist, dass seine Form ein Trio aus Gesichtern bildet. Der unheimliche Blick der Drei dringt dem Betrachter bis tief in die Seele, ganz so als ob hinter den Augen noch immer ein Fünkchen Leben wohnte.
column6: Un pedazo de corteza con la forma de tres rostros. Las inquietantes miradas del trío penetran en tu alma, casi como si existiera alguna clase de espíritu tras sus ojos...

column2: The King James Bible has been the gold standard of all High American bibles for over a millennium. However, only twelve complete pre-Event copies of the King James Bible are known to exist today, and the text is indecipherable without special training.

Once common during festivals in New Orleans, these plastic beads were distributed to anyone who attended these events before the Event. Plastic is now a rare commodity, but not too uncommon, often found by peasants and farmers from time to time.
This golden fencing saber was won from a mysterious stranger clad in black. It is rumored to be imbued with supernatural power, giving its owner the ability to win any sword fight.
This golden falconry glove was won from a mysterious stranger clad in black. It is rumored to be imbued with supernatural power, giving its owner the ability to see through the falcon's eyes.
This golden bow was won from a mysterious stranger clad in black. It is rumored to be imbued with supernatural power, giving its owner inhuman accuracy.
This golden chalice was won from a mysterious stranger clad in black. It is rumored to be imbued with supernatural power, allowing its owner to drink forever without losing their wits.
Tinted glasses from the ancient world, clearer than anything modern craftsmen can produce. Although they do not correct a person's vision, they can effectively shield one's eyes from harsh light.
This little bone is said to have come from one of the ancient liberators of South America.
The Ark, crafted out of shittim wood at God's direction, containing the stone tablets of the Ten Commandments and a pot of manna.
column3: L'Arche, fabriquée en bois d'acacia sur les instructions de Dieu, contenant les tablettes en pierre des Dix Commandements et un pot de manne.
column4: Die Bundeslade, die nach Gottes Anweisungen aus Shittim-Holz gefertigt wurde, enthält die Steintafeln mit den Zehn Geboten und einen Krug mit Manna.
column6: Esta arca, hecha con madera de acacia bajo la dirección de Dios, contiene una jarra de maná y las tablillas de piedra en las que se grabaron los diez mandamientos.

column2: This little pointer is said to have belonged to an incredibly wise and knowledgeable rabbi.
A Shofar once owned by the Lubavitcher Rebbe, the last great pre-Event Chabad Rebbe. While he was alive, some believed he could have been the Moshiach  and some still believe that he is.

These small black leather boxes contain scrolls of parchment with Torah verses inscribed on them. This tefillin dates to before the Event, and, although it is too fragile for everyday use, it is still a valuable item.

The multicolored beads on this necklace represent each of the primary Orishas, and represent a point of contact with each Orisha. They are sacred items in the Yoruba-derived syncretic faiths of the Caribbean and beyond.
This codex contains a surprisingly large number of small portraits featuring the Founders, the Statue of Liberty, and other Americanist holy icons.
This strikingly-detailed portrait depicts one of the ancient Presidents. It is said that this portrait may give advice to worthy rulers if asked in a time of need.
This expensive-looking set of false teeth once belonged to George Washington himself. It features teeth made of ivory set on a wooden frame and held together by golden springs.
This cloth banner is said to have been sewed by Betsy Ross herself and was carried by the original patriots during their battles against the dreaded redcoats in the early days of America.
The legendary companion to the Declaration, this document was once thought lost to time. Although the text is now illegible, it still contains the very soul of America.
This peculiar pre-Event watch uses the power of the Holy Atom to light up in the dark, allowing one to read it at any hour and in any environment.
This device makes a noise when in the presence of the Holy Atom. As the Atom can be neither seen nor felt, it is a highly sacred and useful tool.
This collection of substances constitutes a particularly strong and potent vessel of the Holy Atom, and as such should be treated with the utmost care and respect.

This vessel of the Holy Atom is particularly strong, but it has a reputation of cursing those who attempt to bless themselves with it. Although it still contains the power of the Atom, many view it with distrust and scorn.
This codex contains a surprisingly large amount of coinage. Surely, whoever compiled this codex must have been a high priest of the Almighty Dollar!
Issued by the Holy Mint during the days of old America, this single piece of paper contains the power of many thousands of dollars.
Issued by a temple of the Almighty Dollar in the American Southwest shortly before the Event, this ordinary-looking disc is actually made of highly precious and valuable metals.
A fragment of the Cross Jesus was crucified upon
column3: Un fragment de la Croix sur laquelle Jésus a été crucifié.
column4: Ein Teil des Kreuzes, auf dem Jesus gekreuzigt wurde.
column6: Una parte de la cruz en la que se crucificó a Jesús.

column2: A finger belonging to St. John the Baptist. St. John was a prophet of the Messiah, and was also the one to baptize Jesus.
column3: Un doigt appartenant à saint Jean-Baptiste. Saint Jean était un prophète du Messie, et fut aussi celui qui devait baptiser Jésus.
column4: Ein Finger des hl. Johannes des Täufers. Johannes der Täufer war ein Jünger des Messias, von dem Jesus getauft wurde.
column6: Un dedo perteneciente a san Juan Bautista. San Juan fue un profeta del Mesías, y también fue quien bautizó a Jesús.

column2: This massively ornate tome was one of the first Bibles to be manufactured without papal oversight, and it is therefore holy to those denominations of Christendom that do not recognize papal authority.
This ordinary-looking piece of limestone is said to be the very stone upon which the Holy Cross was raised during Jesus's execution.

This silver-plated church bell is holy to both Anglicans and Métis, and these two groups have warred over its possession for centuries. It is no longer possible to tell who possessed it first or how its current owner came to hold it.

This glass case contains a single rugged black hair. Pirates from Haiti to Newfoundland will recognize it as being part of the legendary Black Beard of Edward Teach, and will treat it with the reverence it deserves.
This simple map has existed for as long as piracy itself, and the large red X on it indicates the precise spot at which an ancient pirate buried his treasure.
This chest of booty was found using an ancient treasure map, and it certainly deserves the reputation it has built up over the centuries.
A fragment of the flagship Blackbeard used to plunder his goods from the dreaded redcoats.
This bizarre-looking skull is made of a single piece of crystal. Although its precise origin is hotly-debated, nobody doubts its divine nature.
This codex was compiled by the ancestors of the Nahua in the days before the colonizers conquered Mexico, and contains an accurate account of pre-arrival Mesoamerican culture.
This headdress once belonged to Motecuhzoma Xocoyotzin himself, and was on his head when he was captured by the conquistador Cortés. It now inspires Mesoamerican warriors on the field of battle.

This idol depicts America Kokudo Kunitama-no-Kami, divine protector of the North American continent. Although not originally Californian in origin, it has been part of the Cetic pantheon since the days of Emperor Elton.

This dazzling jewel-encrusted slipper is said to possess supernatural qualities  if one manages to find both shoes, they can can be used to instantly transport someone "home" by clicking their heels thrice.

This golden falcon is said to have been crafted on a mythical island in the Old World, and was thought to be lost to time. People can and have gone to great lengths to get their hands on this priceless treasure.
This simple but well crafted katana was wielded by Emperor Elton himself throughout his life, and it is said to be enchanted with the authority of heaven itself.
This long shafted spear was said to be the lance of the General of Gaia, crafted from the same redwoods set fire to in the Green Sash Rebellion.

This cross-section of a redwood tree was collected prior to the Event and marked along the rings with numbers indicating how old each part of the tree is. It is a useful reference for discovering tree ages today.
This crystal glows with an otherworldly energy, and can ward off even the most serious of illnesses if applied to the site of pollution for long enough.
Although this wreath of flowers appears to be normal at first glance, none of the flowers decorating it have ever so much as wilted.
This wooden core is no ordinary cross-section  it is part of the legendary tree Methuselah, and is thus older than any religion on this continent.
This peculiar-looking artifact is said to be supercharged with healing energy, allowing its wearer to heal injuries and recover from illness with ease.
This feather headdress belonged to a legendary Native warrior long before the Event, and was worn in ancient battles against the colonizers.
This medicine cord was crafted by an Apache medicine man before the Event. It is made of animal hide and punctuated with beads and shells.
This firearm once belonged to the legendary Lakotah chief Sitting Bull, and was used in his war against the Americans. It was the last Lakotah rifle to be surrendered to Americanist forces.
The skull of the legendary Apache medicine man Geronimo, unjustly taken by a secret Americanist society long before the event. It has now been returned to its rightful owners.
This intimidating-looking instrument produces a tone that sounds eerily similar to a person screaming in pain. Mesoamerican natives use them on the field of battle to intimidate their foes.
It is said to have once belonged to a great Emperor. \nWriten upon its blade are words "Light to raise, weighty to descend."
Once it spat fire and lead on enemies of your kin. \nNow it is merely a reminder of what was lost.
This row of beads is used by devotees of the Virgin Mary to ensure that prayers are said in the proper order. This particular chain of beads is several centuries old.
This legendary sword was wielded by the great King Arthur himself during his campaigns in Britain and beyond. It was once thought lost to time, but it has once again found a worthy bearer.

This firearm is shrouded in mystery and myth. Some say it was wielded by legendary cowboy Jesse James, while others claim this same gun was used to kill him. All, however, agree that it is supernatural in some way.
This pen was used by the god of poetry and redemption, Black Bart. In all his days of banditry, the eloquent Black Bart never took a single life, but gave his own to slay the beast of Far-Gone-Wells.

These feathers were stolen by Sly Coyote when Roadrunner was still a hatchling. Though much of the Frontier's magic has left, they are still as brilliantly colored as when Coyote used them to steal the moon.

This stake was put down by Iron Horse when he crossed the world, gifting mankind an immovable road to gird the earth. With the help of his servant, the Mancho, he forged this stake as a sign of the gods' covenants with humanity.
This horseshoe is said to bring good fortune to anyone who possesses it and hangs it up right side up. Beware  accidentally hanging it the other way will cause one's fortune to vanish...

This intimidating skull once belonged to a Terrible Lizard, a type of beast that roamed the Earth alongside man in the days before the Event. The tales about them seem far-fetched, but this skull proves that they really existed.

This handgun seems crude and ineffective compared to most surviving pre-Event examples, but this piece was manufactured in the modern day. Perhaps one day we can make them like we used to...

As one spins this beautifully engraved little device, a tiny metal needle will always point towards the northern lodestar. Ancient examples are smaller, but this one somehow manages to be more consistently reliable.
The Imperial Crown of the Holy Columbian Confederacy, an octagonal hoop showered with precious stones, representing dominion over all Southrons.
The Imperial Crown of the Holy Columbian Confederacy, an octagonal hoop showered with precious stones, representing dominion over all Southrons.
Once the crown of the Emir of Socal, it has now become a symbol of the Emperor's authority over all of California.
The sacred feathered headdress worn by [thelemic_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s representative in America.
The wooden crown worn by [celtic_pagan_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s divine representative on Earth.
The wooden crown worn by [aria_de_machete_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s divine representative on Earth.
The sacred feathered headdress attuning the wearer with the pantheon and the courts.
The uncomfortable crown worn by [revelationist_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s divine representative on Earth.
The branched crown worn by [occultist_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s chief diviner on Earth.
The branched crown worn by [raven_tales_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s chief diviner on Earth.
Regalia representing the dignity and power of the divine representative of [midewiwin_reformed.GetHighGodName].
The leather crown worn by [trailwalker_reformed.GetHighGodName]'s chief diviner on Earth.
An priceless totem representing Raven, the trickster god of the Haida.
An elktooth totem representing Ta'xet, the Haida god of violent death.
A wooden tube filled with small pebbles and enchanted with ancient spirit-magic.
column3: Un tube de bois rempli de petits cailloux et enchanté par de la magie ancienne.
column4: Ein Holzrohr, dass mit kleinen Kieselsteinen gefüllt und alter Geistermagie verzaubert ist.
column6: Un tubo de madera lleno de guijarros y encantado con antigua magia espiritual.

column2: A mysterious book dealing about the strange spheres beyond. Although most shun this book, those of the [occultist_reformed.GetName] faith know its true value...
It is said that anyone who wields this bow will never miss a shot, so long as their intentions are pure. Some speculate it may have once belonged to Missus Sureshot herself...
This strange charm is carved out of Whale bone. The runes on it are said to bring luck and health to its owner, though the superstitious may fear its power.
This simple knife was carved from a Whale bone. It won't match steel but is a fine mark of status and power.
This fancy necklace was carved from a Whale Bone. It is an impressive symbol of wealth and power.
This icon is an almost perfect recreation of a great religious icon from the distant past.
This religious icon masterfully blends traditional and non-traditional artistic elements.
This antediluvian sword was rediscovered by Leonidas I and now serves as a symbol of the Holy Columbian Confederacy's divine authority.

When Thor was killed during Ragnarok, his hammer shattered and pieces of it fell to earth. Its remnants were gathered and used to repair a legendary pre-Ragnarok trophy given to only the most worthy warriors. It can no longer be used as a weapon, but it still holds great power...
column3: Un marteau étrangement court dont on pourrait croire que sa création a été défectueuse. Il a une ressemblance frappante avec le marteau de Thor, le Dieu du Tonnerre, comme dit dans le mythe.
column4: Ein Hammer mit ungewöhnlich kurzem Stiel, der beinahe so wirkt, als handele es sich um einen Fehler bei der Fertigung. Er weist eine unverkennbare Ähnlichkeit mit dem Hammer auf, den der Donnergott Thor den Mythen zufolge verwendet.
column6: Un martillo extrañamente corto que da la sensación de ser defectuoso. Tiene un parecido sorprendente con el martillo manejado por Thor, el dios del trueno, tal y como lo describe la leyenda.

column2: The weapon of choice of the undead Juan Machete. One of the many treasures hidden by him before taking his spectral form.
The harp used by Florentino in his legendary musical duel against Satán. The sound of the harp is said to reach all victorious commanders.
The mantle used by La Sayona. The fabric seems to be the only physical aspect of the mysterious apparition.
Old relic of the Nasar family. It was stolen by the Vicario brothers and used to murder the last Nasar Duke as revenge for defiling their sister.
Taken by Duke Ibrahim Nasar during the sack of Bogotá. The sacking marked the end of the Kingdom of Andina.
Taken from the burned body of Zacarías I by his killer, king Santiago of Venezuela.
Personal seal of Jorge Isaacs, founder and only ruler of the Republic of Antioquia. It has a mysterious star engraved on it.
The sword used by Simón Bolívar, known as Saint Peter, to cut the ear of one of the men who tried to arrest the Divino Niño.
The kidney stone that killed Francisco Santander's mortal body. His physical dead allowed him to transcend as Saint Francis.
Collar that Manuelita Sáenz wore when she was saved by the Divino Niño from an angry crowd who tried to stone her.
The day on which the próceres stole this relic from the perfidious demon Pepe Botella marks the beginning of the Golden Age of the Patria Grande.
This mummified piece of skin that resembles a pig tail is said to come from the lower back of the Marquees of García, the mad prophet from the Golden Age.
We must honor our holy men and those who live in a pious way to earn the favor of The Light and The Serpentine God.
We must remain steadfast in our faith and firm towards the heathens, for it is the only way to ensure our continued survival. In the name of the Omnissah!
We must develop ever-more complex and esoteric means of ascertaining the Old Ones' will, for if we fail to appease them it will mean the end of this world.
Our queen demands the blood of the infidels, for it is the only way to ensure that we remain the supreme rulers of the waves. Rule Britannia!
Our faith was almost wiped out in the recent past. We must fight back against the heathens, or we shall once again face utter destruction.
Our gods have always permitted us to consort with those of other faiths and allowed righteous mortals to ascend to their ranks. It is high time we revived these practices.
In addition to transforming our existing animistic tradition, we must acknowledge the spiritual equality of men, women, and all other followers of Midewiwin.
We must not allow ourselves to become weak and flabby in this new land. We must continue our campaign of invasion until our supremacy stands unquestioned.
Now that we have established a strong foothold in these new lands, we must focus on maintaining it. Our campaign of invasion must give way to stable and prosperous rule.
We must stay in touch with the spirit of the Frontier and honor those who came before us if we are to have any hope of following the Trail.

For eons our people have been divided among those who admire the strength of the male and those who trust the grace of the female. This divisive barbarism must be left behind as our faithful accept that both the mare and the stallion are necessary for the cavalry to succeed.
Openly Rust Cultist or Chrome Cultist
Openly Aria de Machete or reformed
The helmsman is in charge of ensuring that ships maintain a steady course.
The rum runner is in charge of procuring and distributing alcohol to sailors.
The shipwright is in charge of keeping all vessels is shipshape.
The first mate is the captain's closest confidante, and is typically given to a nautical realm's designated regent.
The second mate keeps watch while the captain sleeps and is responsible for ensuring that the ship remains safe.
The third mate is responsible for keeping the ship's cargo and crew safe in the event of an emergency.

Maintaining contact with a mother empire several thousand miles away is an arduous task that usually cannot entirely be filled out by the Governor of the Colony, who is tasked with ruling. The Colonial Overseer is a high-ranking Court Official tasked with managing the logistics of the Colony and their relations to its homeland.

A title stemming back since before the event, the Sei-i Taishogun is a martial position usually delegated to a skilled commander. Directly translated as "General of the Expeditionary Force against the Barbarians", the commander is tasked with researching the New World and combatting the strange people of this land.

The Nousthreskeia philosophy heavily revolves around the belief of the Noosphere  and believing that people possess a strong mental power that can alter the reality around them. The Evoker of the Will is usually a philosopher of talent who possesses great mastery of this art, and is highly respected in Nousthreskeia tradition.

The Gaian faith places great importance and stress on the woman's contribution to society, believing their role to be of proeminance and preservation. Therefore, to be appointed a Venerable Elder is an honor to Gaian women.

Gardening holds an interesting place in Gaian society, where it is viewed in a generally favorable light. Tending to plants, a key, living font of the Earth Mother, is seen as a sacred duty, and to be the Mistress of the Gardens is an honorable role for any Gaian woman or man.

With most Gaian cities, temples and castles being so integrated into nature, the role of managing the woods is a very important one. The Woodsrunner oversees the management and fusion of the Gaian estate and the environment surrounding it.
Pochtecas serve as judges and arbitrators in Mictlantec realms.
Fire Lighters are responsible for conducting religious rituals, including the important task of lighting the ceremonial fire.
Knights are people worth of the accolade of chivalry, and is part of a lineage of mounted warriors stretching from the ancient cavaliers of Old America to the rough riding retainers of Leonidas..
